<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Volcanic Eruptions Around The World</title>
    <!-- Import Vega & Vega-Lite (does not have to be from CDN) -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vega@5"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vega-lite@4"></script>
    <!-- Import vega-embed -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vega-embed@6"></script>
    <!-- Import pure.css -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/purecss@2.0.3/build/pure-min.css" integrity="sha384-cg6SkqEOCV1NbJoCu11+bm0NvBRc8IYLRGXkmNrqUBfTjmMYwNKPWBTIKyw9mHNJ" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <!-- Google font -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Source+Sans+Pro:wght@400;700;900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- custom style -->
    <style>
      *{
      font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
      }
      h1{
      font-weight: 900;
      text-align: center;
      color: crimson;
      }
      h2{
      text-align: center;
      background-color: lightgray;
      }
      table, th, td {
      border: 1px solid black;
      }
      body{
      background-color: lightgray;
      }
      .page{
      width: 1000px;    
      background-color: white;   
      margin: auto;
      padding: 50px;
      padding-top: 35px;
      }
      .vis-container{
      width: 100%;
      }
      .description h2, h1{
      margin-top:0px;
      }
      .description-right {
      padding-left: 20px;
      }
      .description-left{
      padding-right: 20px;
      }
      .pure-g{
      margin-bottom: 25px;
      }
      .small-font{
      font-size: 14px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-1">
          <h1>Volcanic Eruptions Around The World</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-1">
          <div id="new_symbol_map" class="vis-container"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-1">
          <h2>Local Population of Eruptions</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-3">
          <div class="description description-left">
            <h3>What is Volcano Explositivity Index?</h3>
            <p>The <strong>Volcano Explositivity Index (VEI)</strong> is a relative measure of the explosiveness of volcanic eruptions.</p>
            <table style="width:100%">
              <tr>
                <th>VEI</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Volume of erupted material (km^3)</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>0</td>
                <td>Effusive</td>
                <td>0.00001</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>1</td>
                <td>Gentle</td>
                <td>0.0001</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>2</td>
                <td>Explosive</td>
                <td>0.001</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>3</td>
                <td>Catastrophic</td>
                <td>0.01</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>4</td>
                <td>Cataclysmic</td>
                <td>0.1</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>5</td>
                <td>Paroxysmic</td>
                <td>1</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>6</td>
                <td>Colossal</td>
                <td>10</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>7</td>
                <td>Super-colossal</td>
                <td>100</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>8</td>
                <td>Mega-colossal</td>
                <td>1000</td>
              </tr>
            </table>
            <h3>Which Eruptions are dangerous?</h3>
            <p>The visualisation on the right shows the nearby population of an eruption. Labeled eruptions currently have a large local population and could be devastating.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pure-u-2-3">
          <div id="bubble_plot"  class="vis-container"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-1">
          <h2>Volcano Type Comparison</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-2">
          <div id="box_plot"  class="vis-container"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pure-u-1-2">
          <div id="heat_map"  class="vis-container"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-2">
          <div class="description description-left">
            <h3>Tallest Volcano Types</h3>
            <p>The <strong style="color:#6b6ecf">Compound</strong> volcano type has the tallest volcano. However, the average tallest volcanoes are <strong style="color:#8ca252">Lava cone</strong> types. The <strong style="color:#ad494a">Submarine</strong> volcano types are the shortest since they are below sea level.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pure-u-1-2">
          <div class="description description-left">
            <h3>Dangerous Volcano Types</h3>
            <p><strong style="color:#393b79">Caldera</strong>, <strong style="color:#bd9e39">Pyroclastic shield</strong> and <strong style="color:#e7cb94">Stratovolcano</strong> volcano types have erupted with a VEI of 7 making them the most dangerous volcano types. <strong style="color:#637939">Fissure vent</strong>, <strong style="color:#cedb9c">Maar</strong> and <strong style="color:#d6616b">Tuff cone</strong> have only erupted with up to 3 VEI making them the least dangerous volcano types.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-1">
          <h2>Volcanoes Across Different Regions</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <!-- pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-2-3">
          <div id="new_bar_chart"  class="vis-container"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pure-u-1-3">
          <div class="description description-left">
            <h3>Volcano Infested Regions</h3>
            <p>The region of <strong>Indonesia</strong> and the region of <strong>Japan, Taiwan, Marianas</strong> has had the most volcanic eruptions than other regions. In the last century, <strong>Canada and Western USA</strong> has had the least amount of volcanic eruptions.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- end pure grid group -->
      <div class="pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1-1 small-font">
          <p>This visualisation is created by <a href="https://github.com/kste0015" target="_blank">Kyle Steele</a>. The datasource is <a href="https://www.kaggle.com/jessemostipak/volcano-eruptions" target="_blank">here</href>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- end page -->
    <script type="text/javascript">
      var specVis1 = "js/new_symbol_map.json";
      var specVis2 = "js/new_bar_chart.json";
      var specVis3 = "js/box_plot.json";
      var specVis4 = "js/bubble_plot.json";
      var specVis5 = "js/heat_map.json";
      
      vegaEmbed('#new_symbol_map', specVis1, {"actions": false}).then(function(result) {
        // Access the Vega view instance (https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/api/view/) as result.view
      }).catch(console.error);
      
       vegaEmbed('#new_bar_chart', specVis2, {"actions": false}).then(function(result) {
        // Access the Vega view instance (https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/api/view/) as result.view
      }).catch(console.error);
      
      vegaEmbed('#box_plot', specVis3, {"actions": false}).then(function(result) {
        // Access the Vega view instance (https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/api/view/) as result.view
      }).catch(console.error);
              
      vegaEmbed('#bubble_plot', specVis4, {"actions": false}).then(function(result) {
        // Access the Vega view instance (https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/api/view/) as result.view
      }).catch(console.error);

      vegaEmbed('#heat_map', specVis5, {"actions": false}).then(function(result) {
        // Access the Vega view instance (https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/api/view/) as result.view
      }).catch(console.error);
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
